00:24:57.122 --> 00:24:59.082
Either we need more
evidence or another witness.

532
00:24:59.207 --> 00:25:01.251
How about another rape?

533
00:25:01.376 --> 00:25:04.504
He's done it before. a rape in
a Bronx sublet five years ago.

534
00:25:04.587 --> 00:25:07.090
Same MO. and Burnett
owned the apartment.

535
00:25:12.554 --> 00:25:15.098
The perpetrator held a
knife to the victim's throat

536
00:25:15.223 --> 00:25:17.142
and raped her in the bed.

537
00:25:17.267 --> 00:25:18.768
There was no sign
of forced entry.

538
00:25:18.852 --> 00:25:20.645
and the case remains
unsolved to this day.

539
00:25:20.729 --> 00:25:22.022
Your Honor. at best.
the People have

540
00:25:22.105 --> 00:25:23.773
two rapes five years apart

541
00:25:23.898 --> 00:25:26.276
that occurred in
residences my client owns.

542
00:25:26.401 --> 00:25:28.111
He's owned numerous
apartments in the city.

543
00:25:28.194 --> 00:25:30.071
Two nearly identical rapes.

544
00:25:30.196 --> 00:25:31.906
Your Honor. this
is the definition

545
00:25:31.990 --> 00:25:33.491
of a common scheme or plan.

546
00:25:33.575 --> 00:25:35.452
-It's prejudicial. Judge.
-I agree.

547
00:25:35.535 --> 00:25:38.621
Mr. Carisi. I'm going to
deny your application.

548
00:25:38.747 --> 00:25:43.084
In my view. the prejudicial
effect of this evidence

549
00:25:43.209 --> 00:25:46.004
far outweighs its
probative value.

550
00:25:46.087 --> 00:25:48.548
The prior case is inadmissible.

551
00:25:48.673 --> 00:25:50.925
Gentlemen. tomorrow morning.

552
00:25:53.720 --> 00:25:56.765
I'll draft my motion
to dismiss tonight.

553
00:26:03.992 --> 00:26:05.763
Ella. I know this is not ideal.

554
00:26:05.847 --> 00:26:09.520
And even if we can't find
new evidence tonight.

555
00:26:09.604 --> 00:26:12.566
the fact is that ADA
Carisi can make a motion

556
00:26:12.650 --> 00:26:15.236
to dismiss with a
leave to re-present.

557
00:26:15.320 --> 00:26:17.733
which means we can
bring it back to court.

558
00:26:17.817 --> 00:26:18.569
Okay?

559
00:26:18.653 --> 00:26:20.911
Now. it may take
a little longer.

560
00:26:20.995 --> 00:26:25.168
but I'm not giving up on this.

561
00:26:25.252 --> 00:26:28.386
So yeah.

562
00:26:29.673 --> 00:26:30.882
I'm gonna go home.

563
00:26:32.295 --> 00:26:37.217
So. Ella. you can't
give up on this.

564
00:26:37.301 --> 00:26:39.177
I really... I appreciate
all of the things

565
00:26:39.261 --> 00:26:40.555
that you guys have done.

566
00:26:40.654 --> 00:26:41.988
It's amazing. I
can't believe it.

567
00:26:42.072 --> 00:26:44.658
But it's just...
I just...

568
00:26:44.742 --> 00:26:46.771
What is the best-case
scenario here?

569
00:26:46.855 --> 00:26:49.650
Just getting some guy
deported for testifying?

570
00:26:49.734 --> 00:26:52.066
That sucks. I don't
want to do that.

571
00:26:52.150 --> 00:26:53.985
But that is not our only option.

572
00:26:54.122 --> 00:26:57.459
I don't have anybody
out here with me.

573
00:26:57.784 --> 00:27:00.370
And I just... I want
to get on with my life.

574
00:27:00.495 --> 00:27:04.666
And I am tired.

575
00:27:04.791 --> 00:27:06.835
I'm so tired.

576
00:27:06.918 --> 00:27:10.588
How do you not get so
tired doing this every day?

577
00:27:10.672 --> 00:27:11.965
I couldn't do it.

578
00:27:14.968 --> 00:27:17.012
Did you get the job?

579
00:27:19.848 --> 00:27:20.974
Yeah.

580
00:27:23.643 --> 00:27:25.520
What? You're not taking it?

581
00:27:27.272 --> 00:27:28.940
I don't think so.

582
00:27:29.024 --> 00:27:33.862
Well. are you good
at what you do?

583
00:27:33.945 --> 00:27:36.322
Yeah. but you have this
voice inside that tells you

584
00:27:36.448 --> 00:27:38.408
that you're not good enough?

585
00:27:38.533 --> 00:27:39.534
That you're not worthy?

586
00:27:41.453 --> 00:27:43.664
I get that.

587
00:27:43.747 --> 00:27:47.417
Because I have that
same voice inside.

588
00:27:47.542 --> 00:27:53.506
But I had this really great
boss who believed in me

589
00:27:53.673 --> 00:27:55.384
and who told me
that I was worthy.

590
00:27:57.344 --> 00:28:01.514
And then eventually. I
started to believe it.

591
00:28:03.975 --> 00:28:07.187
He worked a lot
longer than he needed to.

592
00:28:07.312 --> 00:28:10.315
because he was so
good at his job

593
00:28:10.398 --> 00:28:13.526
and because it gave
his life meaning.

594
00:28:13.610 --> 00:28:15.529
He and I were a lot alike.

595
00:28:15.612 --> 00:28:17.447
and I don't think that
I fully realized it

596
00:28:17.530 --> 00:28:20.450
until after he was gone.

597
00:28:20.617 --> 00:28:23.661
I'm sorry.

598
00:28:23.828 --> 00:28:27.999
You are correct. Ella.

599
00:28:28.166 --> 00:28:30.669
These cases are hard.

600
00:28:30.752 --> 00:28:32.962
They're brutal. You're
not wrong about that.

601
00:28:33.088 --> 00:28:36.633
But I am here with you.

602
00:28:36.716 --> 00:28:41.263
It is okay that you are tired.

603
00:28:41.346 --> 00:28:44.599
because I'm not.

604
00:28:44.683 --> 00:28:49.104
And it's okay if you
don't want to fight.

605
00:28:49.270 --> 00:28:51.981
because I'm still
gonna fight for you.

606
00:28:54.693 --> 00:28:57.529
And guess what.

607
00:28:57.696 --> 00:28:59.364
I'm not the only one.

608
00:29:09.416 --> 00:29:11.793
I've been in this
country for 22 years.

609
00:29:11.876 --> 00:29:13.169
I got a job.

610
00:29:13.294 --> 00:29:15.964
I... I'm really good at it.

611
00:29:16.089 --> 00:29:17.882
Paid my taxes.

612
00:29:17.966 --> 00:29:20.593
I send money back to my family.

613
00:29:20.719 --> 00:29:23.597
And I was arrested 15 years ago.

614
00:29:23.680 --> 00:29:25.891
But... but it was for
something that I didn't do.

615
00:29:25.974 --> 00:29:27.309
And we are going
to do everything

616
00:29:27.392 --> 00:29:29.853
that we can to protect you.

617
00:29:29.978 --> 00:29:33.941
So my choices are to... to
run and hide and hope that

618
00:29:34.024 --> 00:29:37.193
they never find me or to...
to just leave my whole life

619
00:29:37.318 --> 00:29:39.237
and just go back.

620
00:29:39.404 --> 00:29:41.489
And now you're asking me

621
00:29:41.656 --> 00:29:43.825
to do something nice
for my government?

622
00:29:43.992 --> 00:29:46.077
Why would I do that?
-You're right.

623
00:29:46.244 --> 00:29:48.997
You're absolutely right.

624
00:29:49.080 --> 00:29:50.707
And if you got up and walked
out of here right now.

625
00:29:50.790 --> 00:29:52.459
nobody would blame you.

626
00:29:52.542 --> 00:29:55.462
But the fact of the
matter is. Mr. Ruíz.

627
00:29:55.545 --> 00:30:00.675
you came in here
tonight. which tells me

628
00:30:00.800 --> 00:30:04.304
that you want to
do what's right.

629
00:30:04.387 --> 00:30:07.766
whether or not you get
something back in return.

630
00:30:07.849 --> 00:30:09.601
Captain. ICE is on the way up.

631
00:30:09.684 --> 00:30:11.770
-What?
-How do they know?

632
00:30:11.853 --> 00:30:14.022
Come. There's a back stairway.

633
00:30:14.105 --> 00:30:15.523
No. wait. Don't try that.

634
00:30:15.607 --> 00:30:16.441
-Can they do this?
-They don't have a warrant.

635
00:30:16.566 --> 00:30:18.235
Doesn't matter. They're Feds.

636
00:30:18.318 --> 00:30:20.112
So they take our witness. and
we can't do anything about it?

637
00:30:20.195 --> 00:30:21.530
Hold on a second. I
need you to trust me.

638
00:30:21.613 --> 00:30:23.615
Can you do that?

639
00:30:25.283 --> 00:30:26.910
Velasco. arrest him.

640
00:30:27.077 --> 00:30:28.661
-What?
-Now.

641
00:30:30.038 --> 00:30:31.957
Arrest him now.

642
00:30:32.040 --> 00:30:33.291
Mr. Ruíz. you're under arrest.

643
00:30:33.375 --> 00:30:34.585
Captain Vincent.
you're interfering

644
00:30:34.668 --> 00:30:35.711
with a federal operation.

645
00:30:35.794 --> 00:30:37.045
Oh. no. she's not.

646
00:30:37.170 --> 00:30:38.546
Jorge Ruíz is a
material witness.

647
00:30:38.713 --> 00:30:40.256
and he's in the
custody of the NYPD.

648
00:30:40.423 --> 00:30:42.223
Do you really want to
help a rapist go free?

649
00:30:42.342 --> 00:30:44.844
He's ours. okay?
Take him to holding.

650
00:30:44.928 --> 00:30:46.680
Once he provides his
testimony... no. no.

651
00:30:46.763 --> 00:30:47.806
We'll release him.

652
00:30:51.643 --> 00:30:53.061
This you?

653
00:30:55.855 --> 00:30:59.610
You have been obstructing this
operation from the beginning.

654
00:30:59.693 --> 00:31:01.986
That is a federal charge.

655
00:31:02.070 --> 00:31:03.488
Put your hands behind your back.

656
00:31:03.571 --> 00:31:05.073
Oh. no.

657
00:31:09.494 --> 00:31:10.870
Captain.
-It's okay.

658
00:31:10.954 --> 00:31:12.581
Stand down. Curry.

659
00:31:12.664 --> 00:31:14.082
Stand down.

660
00:31:46.639 --> 00:31:49.433
The field office director
sends his regards

661
00:31:49.617 --> 00:31:52.912
and. uh. apologizes for
the misunderstanding.

662
00:31:52.996 --> 00:31:55.448
Well. these things happen.

663
00:31:55.532 --> 00:31:56.701
Well. your arrest
is voided. so let's

664
00:31:56.784 --> 00:31:58.327
get the hell out of here. huh?

665
00:32:02.415 --> 00:32:03.710
You're out of your mind.

666
00:32:03.794 --> 00:32:05.124
I'll take
that as a compliment.

667
00:32:05.207 --> 00:32:06.835
And she's a genius.
but she's a lucky one.

668
00:32:06.918 --> 00:32:08.544
Judge Fitzsimmons
owes me a favor.

669
00:32:08.628 --> 00:32:10.423
He agreed to sign off on
the material witness order.

670
00:32:10.506 --> 00:32:12.842
but I gotta get it to him now
to ink so that we're covered.

671
00:32:12.926 --> 00:32:14.558
But. uh. I'll see you later?

672
00:32:14.642 --> 00:32:15.167
-Okay.
-All right.

673
00:32:15.251 --> 00:32:16.576
Buy the jailbird
a drink. will you?

674
00:32:16.659 --> 00:32:17.818
Mm.

675
00:32:17.902 --> 00:32:19.112
Really. congratulations.

676
00:32:19.196 --> 00:32:20.739
That was an incredible save.

677
00:32:20.823 --> 00:32:23.242
Well. it'd probably be better
if I didn't get arrested

678
00:32:23.326 --> 00:32:25.824
before every case.
but. um. your husband

679
00:32:25.908 --> 00:32:28.452
is very good at his job.

680
00:32:29.139 --> 00:32:31.600
I got something sensitive I
need to talk to you about.

681
00:32:31.684 --> 00:32:32.538
Okay.

682
00:32:32.622 --> 00:32:34.182
I haven't even talked
to Sonny about it.

683
00:32:34.732 --> 00:32:36.942
What? What's going on?

684
00:32:37.026 --> 00:32:41.198
Uh. look. in a normal
circumstance. I would...

685
00:32:41.322 --> 00:32:42.906
I would directly go
to Fin with this.

686
00:32:42.990 --> 00:32:44.992
But I don't know
what else to do here.

687
00:32:45.169 --> 00:32:48.047
What about Fin?

688
00:32:48.131 --> 00:32:51.384
So Bruno and Velasco.

689
00:32:51.468 --> 00:32:54.763
they walked into this
bar that Intel has

690
00:32:55.100 --> 00:32:57.060
under surveillance
for drug dealing.

691
00:32:57.143 --> 00:33:00.165
Yeah. they're probably
looking into Fin's assault.

692
00:33:00.249 --> 00:33:03.044
And we have somebody inside.

693
00:33:03.128 --> 00:33:07.466
Did you... did you know
that Fin lost his gun?

694
00:33:14.351 --> 00:33:17.691
Uh. no. I did not.

695
00:33:17.775 --> 00:33:20.487
Look. if we hadn't had
somebody in this bar.

696
00:33:20.571 --> 00:33:22.625
this probably would
have all gone away.

697
00:33:22.709 --> 00:33:24.502
Listen. this is a
confidential report.

698
00:33:24.586 --> 00:33:27.952
No one else is
going to see this.

699
00:33:28.355 --> 00:33:33.151
I just figured enough people
were keeping you in the dark.

700
00:33:38.711 --> 00:33:40.422
Do you swear or affirm
that the testimony

701
00:33:40.506 --> 00:33:42.092
